about:
Living Avenue is selling a Korean cooking pot under the brand Cookerlogy. This pot can only be cooked in a microwave and heats the food on the plate up to 700 degrees in just 3 minutes in the microwave. I call it the 'New Air Fryer'. Air Fryer boasts that it's healthy because no oil is needed and so does the Cookerlogy pots.The healthy cooking edge along with the easy preparation makes it perfect for busy moms (which is who they are targeting at the moment through ambassadors like Amber Chia) but also to the single men and women (yet to explore). 

The main goal for this account is really just to drive sales. The website has an info card that would be very helpful for understanding the product. They've ran this before on their own with a add to cart of RM14.68 and a 4% click through rate. We'll be using their ad account and their hope is to be able to sell 20-30 pots a month to breakeven, they will allocate around RM1500 ads budget and we can use contents with their ambassadors in it to help attract fans.

about:
Pertubuhan ini bergerak pada peringkat awalnya dengan nama SYRIA DI HATIKU yang merupakan salah satu sayap dari Pertubuhan Sinar Damsyik Malaysia (PERSIDAM), yang dibina sebagai kesinambungan tradisi ilmu ulama di Syria. Skop utama Persidam ketika itu menanungi dan menguruskan beberapa institusi pendidikan di Malaysia. Bergerak bersama aktiviti pendidikan ini aktiviti-aktiviti kemanusiaan.

Setelah bergerak seiring bersama beberapa tahun, demi mengembangkan lagi dua misi ini menjadi lebih luas, Ahli Jawatankuasa Persidam memutuskan untuk mengasingkan projek kemanusian bergerak dengan sendirinya atas nama Pertubuhan Peduli Insan Malaysia (Insan Care) yang diasaskan pada tahun 2018.

Ketika ini, Insan Care tidak lagi menumpukan kerja kebajikan khusus untuk satu negara sahaja,  bahkan berkembang dalam kerangka yang lebih luas meliputi negara-negara lain yang juga memerlukan bantuan dan sokongan kemanusiaan.

about:
Opus is an asset management company that has been around for over 15 years, RM7billion asset managed. This is also the company the band lead of Kyoto Protocol, Fuad, works as his full-time job. They specialise in fixed income assets, like bonds, that are long-term in perspective, naturally making them more cautious. 

One of the biggest barriers to investment is the cost. Typically only people who have sufficient disposable income would invest - because this is money you can put aside and could afford losing. But now, they have launched Opus Income Plus Fund for this campaign, where a person could invest with as low as RM100. The management fees are also below 1%. 

The uphshot is that they need to advertise and allow purchasers to complete the process online. Minimising the marketing and sales cost is the only viable way for a retail product. Much like ours.

Besides working with individuals (B2C), they also work with developers with real floorplan of their properties and give us as a feature to buyers. They also, work with furniture stores so you can pick and drop certain furnitures into your design, SofaX then gets a cut from the sales generated. Our engagement with them will be to drive app downloads.

We also discussed about how to best showcase the functionality of the app and they said videos would work best. Since they are opting for a no-video package, they will be providing the videos for our usage. Some examples of contents we can do is a subtle before and after content like an empty home and a visualized home kinda thing. 

Target audience: First time home owners, people who want to renovate their homes
And, we're using their ads manager

about:
Timothy is also the director of Oximas, and he owns (I think), 2 malls in Sarawak. One of the malls that he will be working on is called Hock Lee which is a mall and hotel. What Timothy wants to do is slightly ambitious, he wants to recruit brands in West Malaysia to operate in his malls, so the ads will be aimed to generate interest of businesses to operate in Kuching. He's also ready to supply support like manpower and equipments like remote cameras so that the brands can monitor/train the staffs in Kuching itself. 

The approach to this will be through screened leads. It's important that the business is not some random new business but a trialed and tested one before venturing to Kuching. The account manager should also go through with Timothy on the screening questions which should include asking the business's revenue in the past month. If this works, he will do the same campaign for his other mall in Bintulu called City Point.

about:
Armorproof (www.armorproof.asia) is a brand selling functional foods and drinks. They are very proud of the scientific research that has gone into developing their products, and they sincerely believe that their product can help improve life for millions of unhealthy Malaysians.

Basically how the functional food/drinks work is they combat insulin resistance, which they claim is the main reason people become susceptible to a range of different diseases (https://www.armorproof.asia/insulin-resistance). 

We will be producing 6 collaterals a month. The main objective is educating the market on the science behind the product. Once this is done, we can embark on conversions. The PICs are a bit old-fashioned and usually cannot stop talking, so just keep that in mind.

about:
Otta is an online seller of skincare and beauty brands directly sourced from foreign suppliers. Their brands centre on being simple and 'no bullshit' - straight-to-the-point natural stuff that makes you feel good.

They launched in December 2020, but have been quite satisfied with the amount of sales they've been able to generate so far. 70% of sales so far has been from Malays.

So far, the content they've produced on their own has been very professional (check out their website - https://otta.my/). Their problem has been more from a manpower side (not enough time or people to get contents out on time), so we need to bear that in mind.

Our objective is to get website sales. They also want to make use of the photoshoot services (they saw the YUVA ones and loved it). If all goes well, they'll also look towards ordering a video (they saw the ERKE vids and loved it).

On the whole, they are very friendly and positive people to speak to. Account manager is to have kickoff on 18/5 at 3PM.

about:

about:
"Masala Wheels is a social enterprise that is well known in the NGO space in helping the marginalised by giving them jobs or skills. Their banana leaf rice shop in PJ helps give culinary skills and job opportunities to the poor. What they want is to emphasise the part of them being a social enterprise. When people think of Social Enterprise, they want people to think of Masala Wheels. 

Brief: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1VeRF33eF4cwdI6mwbHDeHy-eVp9I-Z_kqMe2W2axDOE/edit 

Package: 5 posters per month + RM500 ads budget. 
(for first month only, add another RM500 ads budget for ONE post that talks about their current Covid program of giving free meals to the needy)

For the 5 posts per month, use 2 for emphasising social enterprise (the people's stories that they've helped), 2 for their catering business (food), and 1 for capacity building leads (people who want to sponsor them to help needy people get skills)
** Except for the first month, take one post out for the free meals program. "

about:
"Hafiz started Optiqhost as a means for generating additional income, with the business revolving around offering VPS servers. 

Hafiz started Optiqhost after discussions with his Forex friend, who told him that a lot of Forex traders require large server capacity around-the-clock in order for trades to be done efficiently & effectively. Hafiz also started offering out Highway EA (a forex trading system) for free to Optiqhost customers - although he doesn't want to publicly mention this. 

Optiqhost is doing well - with 70k to 100k sales a month. There's also a flourishing community with Telegram groups that provide support & FAQs on their own. 

Hafiz has 3 campaign phases in mind. Phase 1 will be to redo the Optiqhost image (brand awareness - simple content, not too corporate). Phase 2 will be to find affiliates who can provide referrals. Phase 3 will be to generate direct sales.

He has big ambitions of expanding rapidly abroad (at the moment he has Korean & Brunei customers), so the team is to advise him along the way of where to expand the campaign and how much to spend."

Once you’re in the community, you will be given briefings and exclusive first dips on properties at a below market price. The reason why you get these cheap prices is because the group purchases in bulk (sometimes up to 500 units) from the property developer and some of the properties are also leftover units that are not sold yet. En Shafiq’s job is to get people to join the webinar and whenever somebody signs up, he gets 1k as commission.

about: Pure Spectrum sells sim cards under https://www.facebook.com/myfon2u/. They want to target high schoolers from 12-19 years old in conjunction with the government's Pakej Remaja Keluarga Malaysia that offers the sim card at RM10 a month instead of the telco's minimum of RM30 per month. They actually want to offer their simcard as an alternative to parents so they don't have to buy their kids a phone. But this is only limited to schools where MyFon2U's phone booth is installed. For schools that don't have their phone booth, they can use their sim like a normal sim card. When students sign up for their sim, they also get a personal accident (PA) coverage so that's hopefully an incentive for students to sign up. For the 2 contents for free trial, we should focus on recruiting students, they will compile a landing page where we can direct students there. about: Simplify is a peer to peer internet sharing platform with the aim to support the gig economy as people can now monetize their data/wifi. They do this trilogy strategy by recruiting 'routers' to create supply and deploying them in tourist concentrrated area of in areas where people are working from home. Our main goal for them would be to sell their Starter Pack which is a router and RM98/month internet with no contract and no termination penalty. Their conversion rate at the moment is low even though the inquiry rate is high. They now sell about 60-70 packs a month and aim to grow to 100-200 a month. Once a customer places an order, they get the router the next day. Their target market is the people WFH, SMEs and they don't really target people in Klang Valley because most of them already have wifi, so they opt to target people in smaller towns like Butterworth, Kedah Kulim (research areas with no unifi coverage). He mentioned to do contents in different languages but BM typically converts more. We can follow according to the area we're targeting and the population's native tongue.

Before this, she has been running traffic ads to Shopee. She also did a bit of WhatsApp ads. Our advice previously was to run BA before promoting traffic for specific book titles.

about:
Meridian is a freehold property development in Kluang Johor (https://meridiankluangbarat.com/). There are 3 types of developments - terrace houses from RM460,000; Semi-Ds between RM580,000 to RM680,000; and 4+1s between RM780,000 to RM900,000.

Erik (the PIC) is basically part of the team responsible for selling these properties. In total there are 157 units, and only 70 remaining. But the 70 are almost all the 4+1s, and they've been struggling to sell them off. 

From experience, almost all the sales have been for live-in (because who would want to invest in Kluang I guess, haha). They've also tried to reach out to Singaporeans working in Johor. 

Our challenge is to sell these 4+1 units. 

We are doing 2 FB contents, 1 Google content (either SEM/GDN - to discuss with AM), and 1 YouTube ad.

We are using their ad accounts.

about:
Zuen Tech runs a few companies and Raphael is leading their frozen meal plans business arm. He said they just shot themselves in the foot, because the name of their business is NFT (haha this will either be good or bad for SEO), but it stands for Nutritious, Fast and Tasty Foods. It's completely new and he needs postings to start 1st of April, so we need to work ahead this month. He already has a content calendar ready for the first month that we can follow, moving forward, we'll take over the content calendar planning for him. What he's looking for, is a team that would give him suggestions ie oh I saw this on FB that day, we should explore for NFT! kinda attitude. 

Raphael is someone who is our ideal client, he hates working with traditional agencies because they are too rigid about things like what time to post, because he understands that it doesn't matter if we're running ads. He sounds quite chill and understanding. With frozen food, he wants to break the stigma that frozen food = unhealthy, so that's an important note in content planning. He's also going green with his packaging and that's something he's proud of.
MARA Liner is a famous express bus operator. They have a 3 months sales target set out and our goal is to help them meet it.

about:
Thomson TCM is a traditional chinese medicine centre. They only have 2 people in their marketing team, Stephanie and Hakeem, both cannot speak mandarin. From their findings, most of their clients find them through Google, which makes it the main leads funnel point, my suggestion was to start with Google and do retargeting on social media. 

They engaged a previous agency and had just ended their contract with them, they struggled with 2 things:
